   <mods:abstract>Since Maria has received the packet sent to Jay through Mr. Van Zandt by
            Governor Tichenor (of Vermont), will wait until opportunity to send it. Went to Rye last
            Saturday with her sister; met Peter there. Friends as well as usual. Health is neither
            very good nor very bad. Will try to exercise when the weather improves. Hopes MariaÆs
            operation was efficacious. Is only one blessing less of the many that she has. It
            becomes us to resign to GodÆs will. William leaves college in September; will go to
            Albany. Wishes him to board in a decent private family. If Mr. Henry consents to have
            him, Maria can occasionally inquire about him.</mods:abstract>
